import React, { useState } from 'react' import BookFinder from '../Apis/BookFinder' const AddBook = () => { const [isbn, setIsbn] = useState("") const [title, setTitle] = useState("") const [author, setAuthor] = useState("") const [year, setYear] = useState("") const [publisher, setPublisher] = useState("") const [language, setLanguage] = useState("") const [translation, setTranslation] = useState("") const [tags, setTags] = useState("") const handleSubmit = async (e) => { console.log("submit") e.preventDefault(); await BookFinder.post(`/`, { isbn, title, author, year, publisher, language, translation, tags, }); navigate("/") }; return (
setIsbn(e.target.value)} id="isbn" className="form-control" type="text" />
setTitle(e.target.value)} id="title" className="form-control" type="text" />
setAuthor(e.target.value)} id="author" className="form-control" type="text" />
setYear(e.target.value)} id="year" className="form-control" type="text" />
setPublisher(e.target.value)} id="publisher" className="form-control" type="text" />
setLanguage(e.target.value)} id="language" className="form-control" type="text" />
setTranslation(e.target.value)} id="translation" className="form-control" type="text" />
setTags(e.target.value)} id="tags" className="form-control" type="text" />
) } export default AddBook
